msContents.summary: Collection of prayers for the Prophet Muḥammad and other devotional materials such as a description of his tomb and lists of his names and honorary epithets, divided into 60 sections to be read daily over 2 months. This copy is preceded and followed by 91 lines from Būṣīrī's poem known as al-Burdah (f. 1v-5r, 126v-130v) copied in nastaʻliq. Includes a few marginal notes in Persian.
msContents.textLang: Arabic with some marginalia in Persian

بوصيري، شرف الدين محمد بن سعيد،

msItem.title: Dalāʼil al-khayrāt wa shawāriq al-anwār fī dhikr al-ṣalāh ʻalá al-nabī al-mukhtār.

supportDesc.extent: 130 leaves : 207 x 133 (130 x 66) mm bound to 207 x 133 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto; catchwords on every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed and vocalized. Burdah selections in nastaʻliq in black ink; pointed.

decoDesc.decoNote: Polychrome headpieces in blue, yellow, gold, red, and green over text on first opening (f. 5v-6r); full page polychrome illustrations of the mosque at Mecca (f. 17v) and the Rawḍah at Medina (f.18r); textblock is gold sprinkled and bordered in blue, red, and gold rules; gold roundels punctuate text. Rubrications in red. Page-opening ruled in blue and gold.

binding.p: Lacquered red paper over pasteboard (Type III) with gilt paper inlays on a central medallion and two pendants on the vertical axis, with a blind stamped frame. The central medallion is embossed with the binder's name and a formula of humility: al-ʻabd al-ḥaqīr Hakīm Mullā Khawājah Saḥḥāf. Marbled paper doublure. Green leather spine.

history.provenance: Gift of Gordon A. Block, Jr. (bookplate inside back cover), 1966.
